data.enText: a total number or amount made up of smaller amounts that are collected together
sand or broken stone that is used to make concrete or for building roads, etc.
data.chText: （可成混凝土或修路等用的）骨料，集料

data.enText: in (the) aggregate
added together as a total or single amount
on aggregate
when the scores of a number of games are added together
They won 4–2 on aggregate.
made up of several amounts that are added together to form a total number
or
aggregate demand/investment/turnover
data.chText: 总需求 / 投资 / 成交量

data.enText: an aggregate win over their rivals
data.chText: 以总分战胜他们的对手

data.enText: to put together different items, amounts, etc. into a single group or total
or
The scores were aggregated with the first round totals to decide the winner.
data.chText: 此次得分与第一轮所得总分合计决出胜者。

data.enText: the aggregation of data

means: (可成混凝土或修路等用的)骨料，集料

ex.enText: A large quantity of water is stored in the reservoir.
We import huge quantities of oil each year.
ex.chText: 我们每年进口大量石油。

synonyms.bx: 主要表示某种物质的量。

ex.enText: Dividends for the year amounted in the aggregate to $50, 000.
ex.chText: 该年的红利总计达5万美元。

ex.enText: What is the aggregate of goals from the four football matches?
ex.chText: 这4场足球赛的总进球数是多少?

synonyms.bx: 指把各部分加起来的总数。

ex.enText: He spent a large amount of time in New York.
ex.chText: 他在纽约呆了好长时间。

ex.enText: We need a small amount of fuel.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，主要与表示时间、金钱、物质等的不可数名词连用。

ex.enText: You should reduce your daily dosage of the medicine.
ex.chText: 你应该减少每天的用药量。

ex.enText: Excessive dosage of this drug can result in injury to the kidney.
ex.chText: 这种药使用过量会损害肾脏。

synonyms.bx: 尤指经常性一次用药的剂量。

data.enText: in (the) aggregate
added together as a total or single amount
on aggregate
when the scores of a number of games are added together
They won 4–2 on aggregate.

tr: a sum total of many heterogenous things taken together
material such as sand or gravel used with cement and water to make concrete, mortar, or plaster
gather in a mass, sum, or whole
formed of separate units gathered into a mass or whole
example: aggregate expenses include expenses of all divisions combined for the entire year

tr: composed of a dense cluster of separate units such as carpels or florets or drupelets

value.boxr_value: The adjective and noun are pronounced /'ægrɪgət/. The verb is pronounced /'ægrɪgeɪt/. 形容词和名词读作 /'ægrɪgət/。 动词读作 /'ægrɪgeɪt/。

example.ex: The rate of growth of GNP will depend upon the rate of growth of aggregate demand...
example.tran: 国民生产总值的增长率将取决于总需求的增长率。

example.ex: England have beaten the Welsh three times in succession with an aggregate score of 83-12.
example.tran: 英格兰队已经连续3次打败威尔士队，总比分为83比12。

example.ex: The highest aggregate came in the third round where Leeds and Middlesbrough drew 4-4.
example.tran: 第三局时出现了最高比分，利兹队和米德尔斯伯勒队打成4比4平。

value.def: An aggregate amount or score is made up of several smaller amounts or scores added together.

example.ex: ...society viewed as an aggregate of individuals.
example.tran: 被看成个体集合的社会

value.def: An aggregate is a number of people or things that are being considered as a single thing.

example.ex: Different economies, with different currencies, should not be aggregated to produce uniform policies...
example.tran: 不同的经济有着不同的货币，不应该视为一体以制定出统一的政策。

example.ex: We should never aggregate votes to predict results under another system.
example.tran: 我们绝对不可将选票相加来预测另一种制度下的选举结果。

value.def: If amounts or things are aggregated, they are added together and considered as a single amount or thing.

example.ex: A bigger objection is that aggregation of the results invites distortion.
example.tran: 一种更大的异议是把各种结果集中考虑容易导致曲解。

example.ex: Expenses are deductible only to the extent that in aggregate they exceed 7 percent of gross income.
example.tran: 只有在消费总额超过总收入的7%时才可免税。

value.def: If a number of different things or amounts are considered in aggregate, or in the aggregate, they are considered as a single thing or amount.
If one team beats another on aggregate, it wins because it has a higher total score than the other team after a series of games.
